'''[[پښتو]] ابېڅې'''، لکه د پارسي او د اردو ژبې د ابېڅو په شان د عربي ژبې نه اشتقاق شوې ابېڅې دي چې د هغو غږونو او ځليزو ښکارندويي وکړي کوم چې يوازې په پښتو ژبه کې دي او په عربي ژبه کې نه موندل کېږي. دا هغه ابېڅې دي چې د ځينو تورو، ټکو او يا نښو په ځانګړي کېدو سره د څانګړو غږونو لپاره کارېږي.
{{ژباړل}}
== تاريخ ==
The seventeenth century saw the rise of a polemic debate which also was polarized along lines of script. The heterodox [[Roshani movement]] wrote their literature mostly in the Persianate style called the [[Nasta'liq script]]. The followers of the [[Akhund Darweza]], and the Akhund himself, who viewed themselves as defending the religion against the influence of syncretism, wrote Pashto in the Arabicized [[Naskh (script)|Naskh]], which is the generally used script in the modern era of Pashto with some individualized exceptions, due to its greater adaptability for typesetting. Even lithographically reproduced Pashto has been calligraphied in Naskh as a general rule, since it was adopted as standard.

== پښتو ابېڅې ==
[[دوتنه:2 special pashto letters.png|thumb|200px|د پښتو ابېڅو دوه څانګړي توري: ''{{unicode|ṣ̌in}}'' او ''{{unicode|ẓ̌e}}'']]
په پښتو ابېڅو کې داسې توري شته چې په عربي او يا هم د پارسي ژبې په ابېڅو کې نشته. د ساري په توګه، هغه توري representing the [[retroflex consonant]]s {{IPA|/ʈ/, /ɖ/, /ɺ̡/}} and {{IPA|/ɳ/}} are written like the standard [[Arabic language|Arabic]] te, dāl, re and nun with a "{{unicode|panḍak}}", "{{unicode|γaṛwandai}}" or also called "{{unicode|skəṇai}}" attached underneath, which looks like a small circle: <font size="4">{{unicode|ړ}}</font> ,<font size="4">{{unicode|ډ}}</font> ,<font size="4">{{unicode|ټ}}</font>, and <font size="4">{{unicode|ڼ}}</font>, respectively. It also has the letters {{unicode|ṣ̌in}} and {{unicode|ẓ̌e}} (representing [[voiceless retroflex fricative|voiceless]] and [[voiced retroflex fricative]]s), which look like a sin and reh respectively with a dot above and beneath: <font size="4">{{unicode|ښ}}</font> and <font size="4">{{unicode|ږ}}</font>. The letters representing the [[Voiceless alveolar affricate]] {{IPA|/ts/}} and [[Voiced alveolar affricate]]{{IPA|/d͡z/}} look like a <font size="4">{{unicode|ح}}</font> with three dots above and an hamza (<font size="4">{{unicode|ء}}</font>) above; <font size="4">{{unicode|څ}}</font> and <font size="4">{{unicode|ځ}}</font>, and are also specific to Pashto, although <font size="4">{{unicode|څ}}</font> was also used in the related extinct language of [[Khwarezmian language|Khwarezmian]] to represent both {{IPA|/t͡s/}} and {{IPA|/d͡z/}}. Pashto has <font size="4">{{unicode|ى}}</font> ,<font size="4">{{unicode|ې}}</font> ,<font size="4">{{unicode|ۀ}}</font>, and <font size="4">{{unicode|ۍ}}</font> for additional vowels and [[diphthong]]s as well.

په پښتو ابېڅو کې د عربي ژبې ۲۸ پور شوي توري او د پارسي ژبې ۳ پور شوي توري (<font size="4">{{unicode|چ}}</font> ,<font size="4">{{unicode|پ}}</font>, او <font size="4">{{unicode|ژ}}</font>) شامل دي، پاتې ۱۲ توري د پښتو ابېڅو خپل ځانګړي توري دي.

